                  <bindingDesc>
                     <binding notBefore="1775" notAfter="1838">
                        <p>Probably originally uniformly bound as a set together with <ref
                              target="https://www.fihrist.org.uk/catalog/manuscript_26532"
                                 ><idno>Persian MS 1013</idno></ref> in , which was subsequently
                           rebound, whereas this volume still retains it.</p>
                        <p>Sewn at 2 stations, unsupported, edges trimmed, coloured yellow, with
                           endbands omitted. Covered in full bright crimson goatskin
                              <material>leather</material>, tight-backed, over pasteboards,
                           flush-cut with the edges, but without a flap (Type III binding per
                           Déroche).</p>
                        <p>Subsequently repaired by <placeName
                              ref="http://vocab.getty.edu/page/tgn/7010477" key="place_7010477"
                              >Manchester</placeName> bookbinder <persName role="bnd" key="">William
                              Boddington</persName>, who recased the volume with with marbled
                           endpapers at beginning and end and titled the spine.
                              <material>leather</material>, their excess widths adhered as hinges
                           connecting to the first and last flyleaves to the cover, with strips of
                           paper applied over top to disguise the joins.</p>
                        <decoNote type="binding">Boards decorated with gold-blocked central
                           scalloped mandorlas, detached pendants, and cornerpieces, with blind
                           single lines connecting the last along the board margins. <locus
                              from="Spine" to="Spine">Spine</locus> titled<lb/>
                           <q>VOCABULARY OF VERBS</q>.</decoNote>
                        <!--   <p><dimensions type="binding" unit="mm">
